Daily Dev Log - 12-august-2025

Today, I worked on rendering the side faces and managed to fix that issue. However, a new problem arose: some side faces inside the chunks still weren’t rendering.
Because of this, I spent a lot of time working on the generateMesh function, tweaking the if-else conditions and analyzing the results.
Later, I realized that inside the generateTerrain function, I was assigning the Air type to parts below a certain Y value, which I suspected was causing the problems.
To address this, I added a dirt block and placed dirt blocks below that Y value. However, in the game, the dirt blocks still didn’t show up, and the area beneath the top blocks of my world remained empty.
I wasn’t able to solve this problem within about three hours today, so I will continue working on it tomorrow.

